Preference will be given to sessions that incorporate voices from diverse backgrounds and/or different global communities. How does your session accomplish this?

Laura and Jess have a longstanding commitment to diversity and inclusion. They are champions of community building and open practices. In this session Laura and Jess will share their experiences working openly, being transparent, and using technologies that support collaboration and invite participation. Coming from organizations such as Mozilla, Bocoup and Greenpeace, Laura and Jess have been core contributors and creators of open source projects. They are adept at bringing together local communities to create a global relevance.

What outcome are you hoping to achieve with your session? *
The more concrete, the better. For example, I hope to come up with a prototype for a social platform that encourages open and productive discourse on world events.

Through making and sharing we want to:
	•	Help people understand how to bring an open work mindset to their organizations and projects  
	•	Help connect Creative Commons enthusiasts to activists and establish meaningful human collaboration 
	•	Teach how to do open, distributed design 
	•	Share useful CC licensed resources like the Open Decision Framework and the Open Design Kit 
	•	Find contributors to the Greenpeace / Bocoup collaboration 

Abstract (100 words)

The traditional designer - client relationship is fading away. Bocoup and Greenpeace are redefining this dynamic through the redesign of Greenpeace.org. 

People who don’t identify as designers are being empowered to take on active roles in ideation, design and execution. We will explore how the role of designer has changed and examine the tools we have to support and facilitate this movement.

This session will also look at behaviors that spur cultural shifts. Drawing on experience bringing open practices to Greenpeace International, we will examine the social and cultural norms that make open implementation more or less challenging.

Please provide a longer description with any and all information you would like us to know about your session, the topic, and what it will entail.

From contract negotiation to deployment, we will explore open decision and design frameworks to help you and your organization establish relationships that can achieve global impacts. 

User-driven and community-based design projects impactful and fulfilling. In the redesign of Greenpeace.org the use of the Open Decision Framework, the Open Design Kit and community collaboration is of highest importance. In this interactive session, we’d like to share our experiences in a hands on way. Participants can bring their ideas, their businesses, their strategic directions, and we’ll help them set up structures and processes that invite people in. We’ll give advice, talk through issues and create a working atmosphere that helps people solve real world problems.

